tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, significant proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, bilirubin, glucose, ketones), suggesting acute or chronic renal dysfunction with possible nephrotic features. Blood glucose is normal, but HbA1c is unexpectedly low. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation for renal impairment and further assessment of possible underlying causes.
